 ```
 
+For very large project instruction files, Hermes can compile context on demand
+instead of resending the whole file on every turn:
+
+```yaml
+context_files_mode: full       # historical behavior (default)
+context_files_mode: reference  # bounded heading/lead index + per-turn retrieval
+context_files_mode: sparse     # tiny pointer + per-turn exact-section retrieval
+```
+
+`reference` and `sparse` preserve the source files unchanged. They activate
+only when the session has `read_file` or the deferred tool bridge available;
+otherwise Hermes automatically uses `full`. The environment variable
+`HERMES_CONTEXT_FILES_MODE` can temporarily override the configured value.
+
 ## File Read Safety
 
 Controls how much content a single `read_file` call can return. Reads that exceed the limit are rejected with an error telling the agent to use `offset` and `limit` for a smaller range. This prevents a single read of a minified JS bundle or large data file from flooding the context window.
